Definition: the act of expelling a person from their native land
Example: men in exile dream of hope; his deportation to a penal colony; the expatriation of wealthy farmers; the sentence was one of transportation for life
Synonyms: verb, social, deportation, deport, expatriation, expatriate, transportation, banishment, the, act, of, expelling, a, person, from, their, native, land, men, in, dream, hope, his, to, penal, colony, wealthy, farmers, sentence, was, one, for, life
Category: noun.act
